{
  "texts": [
    "Relativism in the hinge loss helps the discriminator to improve its learning using approximate predictions of the real images as half of the images are fake on average instead of taking them all as real.",
    "This prior training information helps the discriminator to classify and predict the real and fake images more accurately and stabilizes the training of MSG-SAGAN.",
    "An improved FID score of 139.6 is achieved for X-ray image synthesis using the proposed MSG-SAGAN.",
    "This section elaborates on the use of regularization terms with additional loss functions in GANs to stabilize the training of GANs.",
    "Gradient penalization (GP) is used to force the discriminator for producing meaningful gradients."
  ]
}